articles.author: The Associated Press
articles.title: Last-minute candidate José Raúl Mulino wins Panama's presidential election - NPR
articles.description: José Raúl Mulino was set to become the new leader of the Central American nation as authorities unofficially called the race Sunday night after his three nearest rivals conceded.
articles.content:
Presidential candidate Jose Raul Mulino, of the Achieving Goals party, celebrates after winning on the day of the general electing in Panama City, on Sunday.
Matias Delacroix/AP
